Language: Dagaare
Language code: gur
Lines: orth orth-seg gloss translat
Author: Drew Owens, Graham Still
Date: January 17, 2018
Source a: Bodomo, A. B. (1997). The structure of Dagaare. Cambridge: Cambridge Univ. Press.

#=======================#
#      Word order       #
#=======================#

# 1
# Adapted from a:41
# Intransitive example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
badɛr kpie la
badɛr  kpi-e         la
spider die-PERF.INTR FACT
'spider dies'

# 2
# Adapted from a:41
# Intransitive example (no factitive)
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
badɛr kpie la
badɛr  kpi-e
spider die-PERF.INTR
'spider might die'

# 2
# Adapted from a:114
# Transitive example
# SVO
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
a badɛr boɔro la koɔraa
a   badɛr  boɔ-ro   la   koɔraa
DEF spidɛr love-IPFV FACT farmer
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 4
# Adapted from a:114
# Transitive example (no factitive)
# SVO
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
a badɛr boɔro la koɔraa
a   badɛr  boɔ-ro   la   koɔraa
the spidɛr love-IPFV FACT farmer
'the spider might love a farmer'

# 3
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical SOV example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
a badɛr koɔraa boɔro la
a   badɛr  koɔraa boɔ-ro    la
DEF spidɛr farmer love-IPFV FACT
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 4
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical VSO example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
boɔro la a badɛr koɔraa
boɔ-ro    la   DEF badɛr  koɔraa
love-IPFV FACT the spidɛr farmer
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 5
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical VOS example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
boɔro la koɔraa a badɛr
boɔ-ro    la   koɔraa a   badɛr
love-IPFV FACT farmer DEF spidɛr
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 6
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical OSV example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
koɔraa a badɛr boɔro la
koɔraa a   badɛr  boɔ-ro    la
farmer DEF spidɛr love-IPFV FACT
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 7
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical OVS example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
koɔraa boɔro la a badɛr
koɔraa boɔ-ro    la   a   badɛr
farmer love-IPFV FACT DEF spidɛr
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 8
# Adapted from a:42
# Ditransitive
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
naa ko koɔraa la gane
naa   ko        koɔraa la   gane
chief give.PERF farmer FACT book
'I give a farmer a book'

# 11
# Adapted from a:42
# Ditransitive (no factitive)
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
naa ko koɔraa la gane
naa   ko        koɔraa gane
chief give.PERF farmer book
'I might give a farmer a book'

